Steam has officially kicked off its Intergalactic Summer Sale, offering discounts on over 10,000 games within its online store. The specials will be available for 14 days until 19:00 on Thursday 5 July 2018. Steam has also launched the Summer Saliens Game, which users can play for the duration of the event and earn Summer Sale Trading Cards. The game sees players battling aliens across a number of worlds and earning various rewards for taking control of map sectors. Playing the Summer Saliens game will also help unlock free games available for all users. Featured deals for the first day of the Steam Summer Sale include discounts on PlayerUnknownâ€™s Battlegrounds, the Fallout franchise, Tyranny, and more. Featured deals on the Steam Store landing page will change every day, but all game discounts will be available for the duration of the sale. 